        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 6:32PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 631 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles south of Grassland, or 14 miles southwest of Post, moving
southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern Lynn
and southwestern Garza Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
